    "Therefore Pr h ≤ E[h] + dσ h = erf dσ h √ 2σ h = erf d √ 2.",
    "Thus given 1 -erf d √ 2 ≤ 2 δ we have K ′ = ⌈dκ √ 1 -p⌉.",
    "Set K:= K + K ′.",
    "Following the procedure described above, we implemented the following two helper functions:",
    "Probability(Xs, K, log 2 (N), log 2 (M)) → δ: given Xs the secret distribution, K, log 2 (N) and log 2 (M) returns δ = log 2 (Pr [∥I(Y)∥ > K])."
